parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lose power steering assist, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fault warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel wobbles or shakes
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear or rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lose power steering assist, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel wobbles or shakes
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
grinding or rubbing noise when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column or shaft can cause the steering wheel to become loose or wobbly, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel is loose or wobbly
the steering wheel can be moved from side to side or up and down on the column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or hesitate, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or downshifts unexpectedly
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle may experience hard shifting or delayed shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering suddenly fails

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shifter failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The gear shifter is stuck in park

and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
